Application server vs web server:

Web server:
The web server covers only the web container
It is useful or suitable for static content
Consume or use less resources
Organize the execution environment for web apps
Multiple threading is not supported
The capacity is lower than that of the app server
HTML and HTTP protocols are used

App server:
It covers the web container and the EJB container
It is equipped for dynamic content
Use more resources
Organize the runtime environment for business app
multiple threading is supported
The service capacity is greater than the web server
GUI and HTTP and RCP / RMI protocols are used